        "created_at": "2022-11-25T16:20:48.083Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I have not gotten Openvpn to work yet but I do have another question.</p>\n<p>In my region, Internet access might not be the most stable and there could be network disconnection.  Is there a way to make dnstt-client auto reconnect when that happens?  When there is a disconnect, the ncat client can no longer get through to the server side unless I restart the dnstt-client.</p>",
